text.section:
Except as otherwise provided in this section, a person shall obtain a permit with a Grade A or a manufactured grade classification from the Secretary before that person may:
Bring, send, or receive a milk product into this State for sale;
Offer a milk product for sale;
Give a milk product away;
Store a milk product; or
Transport a milk product.

A permit is required to:
Be a bobtailer;
Be a bulk milk hauler/sampler;
Be a certified industry dairy farm inspector;
Be a milk processor;
Be a milk processor - farmstead cheese producer;
Be a milk producer;
Operate a distribution station;
Operate a milk transportation company;
Operate a receiving station; or
Operate a transfer station.
